@startuml
skinparam actorStyle stickman
left to right direction

package "Smart Parking System" {
    usecase "Park Vehicle" as UC1
    usecase "Register Vehicle" as UC2
    usecase "Exit Vehicle" as UC3
    usecase "Pay Parking Fee" as UC4
    usecase "Monitor Parking Lot" as UC5
    usecase "Manage Parking Configuration" as UC6
}

actor "Parking User" as User
actor "System Administrator" as Admin

' This is the Secondary Actor '
actor "Payment Gateway" as Bank <<Secondary>>

' Use solid lines without arrows for Actor associations '
User -- UC1
User -- UC3

Admin -- UC5
Admin -- UC6

' Included use cases use dashed arrows '
UC1 ..> UC2 : <<include>>
UC3 ..> UC4 : <<include>>

' Association with the Secondary Actor '
UC4 -- Bank

note right of User
The Parking User represents any individual who uses the smart parking system 
to park and retrieve a vehicle. This actor interacts with the system to 
register vehicle details, park in an available slot, and pay fees.
end note

note right of Admin
The System Administrator is responsible for overseeing the overall 
operation of the system. This actor monitors parking lot status, 
manages parking rules, and ensures the system operates accurately.
end note

note right of Bank
The Payment Gateway is a secondary actor representing the external 
financial service that processes credit card or digital wallet 
transactions to authorize parking fee payments.
end note

note top of UC1
This use case allows a user to park a vehicle. The system verifies 
registration details and assigns an available slot, updating 
the occupancy status in real-time.
end note

note top of UC2
This use case handles the entry of vehicle information such as 
license plate and vehicle type. Registration is a mandatory 
prerequisite before a vehicle is assigned a spot.
end note

note bottom of UC3
This use case enables the user to leave the lot. The system 
verifies that all fees are settled before releasing the 
vehicle and marking the slot as available.
end note

note bottom of UC4
This use case handles the financial transaction. It calculates 
the fee based on duration and communicates with the 
Payment Gateway to finalize the charge.
end note

note top of UC5
This use case allows the administrator to view the live status 
of the parking lot, including total occupancy, available spaces, 
and any system alerts.
end note

note bottom of UC6
This use case enables the administrator to set parking rates, 
define time limits, and adjust system-wide parameters to 
optimize lot performance.
end note
@enduml
